Opened in 1908, the Sorrento Hotel, is a local landmark that has undergone a makeover. The renovation includes a remodeled restaurant, now called the Dunbar Room. Jared Lovejoy, left, and Jena Thornton, are the designers responsible for the remodel. The remodel includes improved lighting and a new floor with tiles from Morocco. The Seattle Monorail, which was built for the World's Fair in Seattle in 1962, runs on a one-mile route along Fifth Avenue from the Seattle Center to Westlake Center.The monorail travels through the Experience Music Project Museum at Seattle Center.
